<body>
<div type="letter">
<pb facs="1037753" n="11v"/>
<opener><lb/>Viro Excellentissimo et Celeberrimo <rs key="pers_DE-588-118509969" type="person"><abbr>Joh.</abbr> Bernoull<choice><orig><g ref="#j">j</g></orig><reg>i</reg></choice></rs> Patruo suo <abbr>pl.</abbr> colendo
                    <lb/><abbr>S. P. D.</abbr> <rs key="pers_DE-588-119166895" type="person">Nicolaus Bernoull<choice><orig><g ref="#j">j</g></orig><reg>i</reg></choice></rs></opener>
<p><lb/>Non dubito, Patrue honoratissime, Te <rs type="letter">literas</rs> meas, quas <rs key="place_GEO-2660646" type="place">Genev<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> ipso abitus mei die ad Te scripsi, <choice><orig><g ref="#agrav">à</g></orig><reg>a</reg></choice>
                    <lb/><rs key="pers_DE-588-135542286" type="person">Patre</rs> meo accepisse, et ab eo quoque intellexisse, quemnam habuerint Tu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> ad <rs key="pers_DE-588-120052539" type="person">Abbatem Bignonium</rs>
<lb/>et <rs key="pers_DE-588-119062372" type="person">Varignonium</rs> co<choice><orig><g ref="#mm">m̄</g></orig><reg>mm</reg></choice>endatiti<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>, quas nequidem necessarias fuisse ambo asseverarunt judicantes,
                   <lb/>magnam Tui nominis celebritatem mihi ubique pro sufficienti co<choice><orig><g ref="#mm">m̄</g></orig><reg>mm</reg></choice>endatione esse, quod quam
                    <lb/>verum sit, hactenus abunde expertus sum. Illustris <rs key="pers_DE-588-119062372" type="person">Bignonius</rs>, qui me ea qua solet urbanita<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>te excepit, mihique <rs type="organisation">Academiam Regiam</rs> frequentare permisit, novum titulorum suorum
                <pb facs="1037754" n="12r"/>
<lb/>nuper accepit augmentum <choice><orig><g ref="#agrav">à</g></orig><reg>a</reg></choice> munere Ecclesiastico, quod ipsi detulerunt Canonici Sancti Germani
                    <lb/>Episcopi Auxerrensis<!-- Saint Germain-l'Auxerrois -->, qui eum Decanum<!-- gemeint ist Bignon --> capituli sui elegerunt, et reditu annuo decem mille li<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>brarum ditarunt; <abbr>D.</abbr> <rs key="pers_DE-588-122149335" type="person">Homberg</rs> et <abbr>D.</abbr> <rs key="pers_DE-588-118639056" type="person">Fontenelle</rs> ipsi de hoc beneficio <rs type="organisation">Academi<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> nomine hesterno die
                   <lb/>sole<choice><orig><g ref="#nn">n̄</g></orig><reg>nn</reg></choice>iter gratulati sunt. Aliquoties jam interfui conventibus Academicis, sed nihil pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>ter Anato<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>mica et Chymica aut alia, qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> non ad me spectant, audivi; <rs key="pers_DE-588-117619515" type="person">Saurinus</rs>, quem ordo loquendi jam
                   <lb/>ab aliquo tempore tetigit, et qui etiam se venturum promisit, jam aliquot vicibus emansit.
                    <lb/>Nuper lecta fuerunt excerpta<note resp="SG" type="comment">Der Bericht über Marsiglis Schrift <hi rend="i"> Histoire physique de la mer</hi> findet sich in Hist. Paris 1710 (1712), pp. 23-29. Das 1710 fertiggestellte und bei der Académie eingesandte Werk wurde erst 1725 gedruckt.</note> qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>dam ex <rs key="biblio_877R6WBH" type="biblio">Tractatu</rs> aliquo Comitis <rs key="pers_DE-588-118640968" type="person">de Marsigli</rs>, quem haud
                    <lb/>ita pridem <rs key="place_GEO-2995469" type="place">Massili<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> de mari conscripsit et <rs type="organisation">Academi<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> dedicavit; agit in eo pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>cipue de va<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>riis rebus in mari et in fundo maris nascentibus, de variis profunditatibus maris, de aqua et sale
                   <lb/>marinos <abbr><choice><orig><g ref="#pp">pp.</g></orig><reg>etc.</reg></choice></abbr> <abbr>D.</abbr> <rs key="pers_DE-588-117648388" type="person">Cassini</rs> et <rs key="pers_DE-588-117541613" type="person">Maraldi</rs> mihi potestatem dederunt in <rs type="organisation">Observatorium</rs> quandocunque li<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>buerit veniendi, imo etiam mensam suam mihi obtulerunt, ut possem eo facilius altitudinem So<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>lis meridianam cum illis observare; co<choice><orig><g ref="#mm">m̄</g></orig><reg>mm</reg></choice>odam itaque haberem occasionem modum observandi ab
                   <lb/>illis discendi, sed quia procul ab <rs type="organisation">Observatorio</rs> habito, et noctu per Urbem ambulare periculosum
                   <lb/>est, malo domi manere, usque dum socium aliquem qui me comitetur inveniam. <rs type="keyword">Acta</rs><!-- Hist. & Mém. Paris --> <rs type="organisation">Acade<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>mi<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>teriti anni nondum impressa sunt, nec ante tres aut quatuor menses imprimentur; Ty<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>pographi admodum sunt lenti, et <choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>gre imprimunt tales libros, quorum ob miseriam istorum
                   <lb/>temporum tam paucos inveniunt emtores. <abbr>P.</abbr> <rs key="pers_DE-588-117526789" type="person">Reyneau</rs> imprimi curabit additiones quasdan ad
                    <lb/><rs key="biblio_W3CIDLH3" type="biblio">Analysin demonstratam</rs>,<!-- Es konnte keine Publikation ausfindig gemacht werden, die den hier erwähnten additions entspricht. Die zweite Ausgabe der Analyse demontrée erschien erst 1736-1738 (https://www.e-rara.ch/zut/content/structure/5231892) --> in quibus inter alia, ut ab ipso audivi, monstrabit novam et facilem
                    <lb/>methodum construendi logarithmos. <rs key="pers_DE-588-117601020" type="person">Montmortium</rs> nondum videre licuit. Salutant Te Abbas
                   <lb/><rs key="pers_DE-588-120052539" type="person">Bignonius</rs>, <rs key="pers_DE-588-118576682" type="person">Malebrancius</rs>, <rs key="pers_DE-588-118639056" type="person">Fontenelle</rs> et reliqua omnis literatorum cohors; hortantur Te etiam
                   <lb/>et maxime rogant, ut opus aliquod edas, aut saltem nova Tua inventa subinde cum <rs type="organisation">Academia</rs>
<lb/>co<choice><orig><g ref="#mm">m̄</g></orig><reg>mm</reg></choice>unicare digneris; bene facies, si totam motus Tui reptorii, et quam inde deduxisti transfor<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>mationis linearum curvarum in arcus circulares theoriam <rs type="biblio">Actis Academicis</rs> inseri curabis.
                    <lb/><rs key="pers_DE-588-119062372" type="person">Varignonius</rs> Tibi juxta salutem nuntiari jubet, se curaturum, ut ill<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>, quas petis, Clarorum
                   <lb/>Virorum effigies tam cito quam fieri potest depingantur; feri<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> instantes ipsi jam sat otii
                    <lb/>permittent, ut se pictori co<choice><orig><g ref="#mm">m̄</g></orig><reg>mm</reg></choice>odare possit. Pro salute, quam mihi per <add><abbr>D.</abbr></add> <rs key="pers_DE-588-1089647115" type="person">Harderum</rs> <rs key="place_GEO-2658761" type="place">Scaphusiensem</rs>
<lb/>misisti, gratias ago, eamque reciproca rependo salute, quam Tibi, <rs key="pers_DE-588-108991332X" type="person">Uxori</rs> <rs key="pers_DE-588-117589144 pers_DE-588-1153514060 pers_DE-588-118656503 pers_DE-588-1089913494 pers_DE-588-117589136" type="persons">liberisque</rs> Tuis, pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice><pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>sertim <rs key="pers_DE-588-117589136" type="person">filiolo</rs> recens nato animibus apprecor.</p>
<closer><salute>Vale.</salute> <dateline>Daham <rs key="place_GEO-2988507" type="place">Parisiis</rs> <date when="1710-07-30"><choice><abbr>d.</abbr><expan>die</expan></choice> 30. Julii 1710</date>.</dateline></closer>
</div>
</body>
